Parents of the abducted students of the Government Science Secondary School, Kankara on Sunday staged a protest over the sad incident. The protesters marching with placards, called on the Federal Government to immediately rescue their children. Some of the parents held placards with the inscriptions such as ‘Government must speak out’, ‘We want our children back’ and ‘We want security in Kankara’. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-858949" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-3.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="540" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-3.jpg 720w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-3-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"> DAILY POST recalls that the students were abducted by armed bandits in the early hours of Saturday, December 12. The Governor of Katsina state, Aminu Masari confirmed that about 333 students are still missing. The governor, who ordered closure of all schools, assured the residents that the students will be rescued soon. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-858947" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest.jpg" alt="" width="540" height="540" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest.jpg 540w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/protest-80x80.jpg 80w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px">